This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of recommendation. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new modeling network. Additionally, it involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to process user behavior data, which could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also deals with the challenge of cross-domain recommendation, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of smart TV watching logs, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
